cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with audio signal separation and extraction, specifically speech from a variety of different sound and noise classes. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a method for signal extraction and reconstruction using deep neural networks and complex time-frequency filters. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses deep neural networks to estimate the complex time-frequency filters for signal extraction. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper addresses the problem of destructive interference in mixture time-frequency bins and proposes a solution using complex time-frequency filters. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with audio signal separation and extraction, which falls under the domain of multimedia.
